<item>
            <title>[HBASE-11686] Shell code should create a binding / irb workspace instead of polluting the root namespace</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-11686</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Right now, the shell builds a list of commands and then injects them into the root exectution&apos;s context&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;bin/hirb.rb&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
# Add commands to &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; namespace
@shell.export_commands(self)
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;hbase-shell/src/main/ruby/shell.rb&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
    def export_commands(where)
      ::Shell.commands.keys.each &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;do&lt;/span&gt; |cmd|
        # here where is the IRB namespace
        # &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt; method just adds the call to the specified command
        # which just references back to &apos;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;&apos; shell object
        # a decently extensible way to add commands
        where.send :instance_eval, &amp;lt;&amp;lt;-EOF
          def #{cmd}(*args)
            ret = @shell.command(&apos;#{cmd}&apos;, *args)
            puts
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;return&lt;/span&gt; ret
          end
        EOF
      end
    end
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is an unclean abstraction. For one, it requires that there be an instance variable in the main namespace called &apos;@shell&apos; without making that clear in the docs. Additionally, it complicates maintenance by breaking isolation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We should update things so that shell can provide a binding for eval or a workspace for IRB execution and then use it directly when we construct our IRB session.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
